title: College visits
name: College visits
description:
A Map by Qhancock

This map shows all of the colleges that I visited during my junior and senior year in high school

properties.name: Auburn University
properties.description: Posted by QhancockI went to the auburn football camp and I went away impressed. I liked what I saw and everything was good

properties.name: Florida State University
properties.description: Posted by QhancockI came here on a unofficial visit to the FSU Miami game. I knew I wasn\'t going here because I grew up hating the FSU football.

properties.name: Georgia Tech
properties.description: Posted by QhancockI had a lot of fun on this visit but I couldn\'t see myself going here

properties.name: University of Florida
properties.description: Posted by QhancockUniversity of FlaWas the closest college to my home in St. Augustine, FL. I Visited this college many times to see the football games and see the campus.

properties.name: University of Maryland
properties.description: Posted by QhancockCollege Park!I came here on one of my official visits in the winter time and it was freezing. Overall I left impressed and I had a good time.

properties.name: University of Miami
properties.description: Posted by QhancockCoral Gables, FLI had a great time down here in miami. I liked the campus and the atmosphere but i didn\'t think it was right for me.

properties.name: University of Michigan
properties.description: Posted by Qhancockthey had a beautiful campus up here but it was just too cold and too far from home.

properties.name: University of Nebraska Lincoln
properties.description: Posted by Qhancock900 N 16th St, Lincoln, NE, 68508I visited this university the week of a football game against Wake Forest and they won by a large margin. I left this place very impressed and I almost committed here.

properties.name: University of South Carolina
properties.description: Posted by QhancockI had been to this city before but i had never been to the university. I wouldn\'t say I didn\'t like it but I couldnt see myself there.

properties.name: University of Tennessee
properties.description: Posted by QhancockKnoxville, TennesseeWhen I came here it just felt like it was the place for me. I liked everything about it. What really sold me on this place was walking into neyland Stadium. So I committed here on my last official visit
